biography: Weâ€™re for people who love cars and love driving them. We celebrate car culture, treasure the community and help protect your pride and joy.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Hagerty's Christmas Video: The One That Almost Got Away
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Forget John Lewis, this will make you feel good this Christmas! We dare you to watch to the end without shedding a tear... Our movie sees a car dealer stumble across their father's old car. He buys it back, but what happens next is a total surprise. 
We're passionate about making car content that we - as enthusiasts - would like to see. Plus we worked with some great people on the film, including David who stars (who is actually a car dealer! and his real-life dad! Enjoy.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Magnum Vice
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Hagerty loves the 1980s and â€˜90s, when cops wore pastel suits and drove white supercars, and the bad guys were inconspicuous in their Hawaiian shirts and yellow 4x4s. Cool cars, white powder and a car chase... find out whatâ€™s going on in our new video.

Thanks to Duke of London, Mather Collectables, Louis Beausoleil, Charlie Aprahamian and Charles Clegg.

By definition, the mood and tone of any atmosphere is a blend of scene setting, characters, subject or story and engaging all the senses.
Defining it is one thing, but to achieve and experience great atmosphere is no mean feat.

Of course Iâ€™d heard of @caffeineandmachine, the reviews, reputation and hearsay speak volumes for whatâ€™s been achieved since Phil, family and friends established the hedonistic hub. But it wasnâ€™t until I finally visited and experienced their mastery of atmosphere, that it fully sunk in.
It feels like coming home, like a mass gathering of close friends, an instant familiarity of mechanical being, artistic beauty and shared passion.
Throughout each month, the different themed nights add further depth to the unique C&M vibe.

Canâ€™t wait to be rolling into the yard again soon - itâ€™s fair to say I was pretty smitten from the off.

We have a new exhibit coming for a short while.. 1999 Ford Racing Puma, one of 500 made for the UK market.. Built by Tickford, they were nearly as expensive as a Lotus Elise when launched so didn't sell well. Now regarded as one of the best small FWD coupes.
.
.
